Further information about the processing of Personal Data
Schnopsn
Downloading the Schnopsn app
When you download the Schnopsn app, the information necessary for this download is transferred to the respective app store operator (Apple App Store or Google Play). Depending on the app store, this can be your email address or the customer ID of the app store user, at which time the download happened, and the individual device identifier. DonkeyCat GmbH has no authority over this process and is therefore not accountable. Respective privacy policies of the app store apply.
Installation and permissions
In order for the Schnopsn app to run properly and in its entirety, and for the associated services to be provided adequately, Schnopsn needs access to select information and permissions.
Depending on the operating system, a permission to access individual functions and information may be requested during the installation process. The necessary access permissions include notifications, access to photos for the profile picture, and mobile data.
You can personally revoke or grant these authorizations at any time on your device; However, it must be taken into account that the Schnopsn app can only be used to a limited extent or not at all without the according permissions. Depending on the app version, permissions are requested either before or after the installation.
How is my data collected, processed, and used by DonkeyCat when I visit the Schnopsn website or use the Schnopsn app without creating a user profile?
DonkeyCat GmbH uses the personal data that the user communicates or that arise when using DonkeyCat GmbH without creating a user profile, without separate consent exclusively for the implementation of the user relationship and as shown in this privacy policy.
When visiting the Schnopsn website or installing the Schnopsn app without creating a user profile, DonkeyCat GmbH collects the following data transmitted by the user's device or browser:
•	IP address
•	Name of the website, file, date and time of the request
•	amount of data transferred
•	browser type and version
•	Referrer URL: from where the visitor came to the accessed page
•	requesting provider
If you are using our contact form on the website to contact our support, the following data is transmitted via E-Mail to our support team:
- E-Mail
- Schnopsn Username
- Name
- ELO
- Platform
- Your request
All support requests via E-Mail, Contact Form or Helpshift are kept for 365 days in case there are follow-up requests and deleted afterwards.
As well as additionally with the sole installation of the Schnopsn app without registration or creation of a user profile, the following data, which are transmitted from the device or the browser of the user:
•	Push Handle (for sending push notifications)
•	country code
•	language
•	name of device
•	name and version of the operating system.
This data is required to make the best possible use of the website or installation of the Schnopsn app and is also used for statistical purposes for the optimization of Schnopsn. We process and use this data to prevent and combat fake profiles, unlawful acts and spam, and to ensure the integrity and stability of the Schnopsn Platform. Donkeycat also uses cookies and analytical services.
How will my data be collected, processed and used after creating a user profile and using the services of the Schnopsn app?
For display in the app and to provide info for other players
Donkeycat GmbH uses the personal data provided by the user or occurring from the use of Schnopsn after creating a user profile without separate consent exclusively for implementing the user relationship as described in this privacy policy. For the full online gaming experience of Schnopsn it is necessary for the user to create a user profile. For this, it is possible to enter some personal data that Donkeycat GmbH uses to provide the respective service.
Mandatory information for the creation of the user profile
When registering and creating a user profile, the following information must be provided:
•	username (pseudonym)
Furthermore, the following information can be provided voluntarily:
•	e-mail address
• 	password
• 	country and state
• 	date of birth
• 	gender
•	 photo
This information is collected, processed and used for the purpose of using Schnopsn and is publicly visible to all other users, as well as on the website, with the exception of the email address and password.
Among other things, these data are used for addressing the user, for authentication, for age verification, for personalizing the profile, for sending game-relevant information (such as tournament results) and bonus Credits, and as login name.
Game activities
The game activities are stored by Donkeycat as long as the account exists to provide game statistics and a consistent history of Elos and Credits to the user. These activities are purged upon deletion of the profile, or anonymized as far as necessary for data consistency.
IP addresses
The IP addresses of all users are recorded for security and auditing purposes to prevent misuse of the service. The data are processed and used to prevent and combat fake profiles, unlawful acts and spam, as well as to ensure the integrity and stability of the Schnopsn Platform.
Chat history during the game
The Schnopsn app offers the possibility to chat with the opponent during a game. The history of this chat is recorded by us for security and auditing purposes and stored for 30 days to sanction misconduct.
Messages in the Message Center
Messages sent from the user's account or sent to the user from other accounts can be deleted by the user at any time.
Deleting the account
The user can delete their own profile from us at any time and without stating any reasons or delete it themselves in the app. If the account is deleted, the existing data will also be partially anonymised for reasons of integrity.
Payment data
In-app purchases through Schnopsn, purchase of Credits (the in-game currency) or the purchase of our paid, ad-free Schnopsn Pro App, are handled through external payment providers. DonkeyCat GmbH does not collect and process any payment data when making a purchase. The input and processing of the payment data takes place directly with the payment providers. The only data exchanged between DonkeyCat GmbH and the payment providers is technical data (including the transaction ID) used to validate the purchases.
Your rights
You inherently have the rights to information, correction, deletion, restriction, data portability, revocation and opposition. If you believe that processing your data violates data protection law or if your data protection claims have otherwise been violated in a way, you can complain to the supervisory authority. In Austria, this is the Data Protection Office.
Contacting us
If you contact us through a form on our website or by e-mail, the data you provide will be stored for six months in order to process the request and in case of follow-up questions. We will not share this information without your consent.
You can reach us under the following contact details:
DonkeyCat GmbH
Heinestraße 40/21
A-1020 Vienna
office@donkeycat.com
DonkeyCat App
How are my data collected, processed, and used when downloading the app?
Downloading the App
When downloading the app, the necessary information is transferred to the respective app store operator (Apple App Store or Google Play). Depending on the app store, this may include the app store user's email address or customer number, the time of the download, and an individual device identifier. DonkeyCat GmbH has no control over this process and is therefore not responsible for it. The relevant privacy policies/settings of the respective app store operator apply.
Installation and Permissions
For the app to function correctly and fully and to provide the associated services adequately, Schnopsn requires various access rights and information.
Depending on the operating system, permission for access to certain functions and information may be requested during the installation process. The necessary access permissions include notifications, access to photos for the profile picture, and mobile data.
You can revoke or grant these permissions at any time on your device; however, it should be noted that the app can only be used to a limited extent or not at all without the necessary permissions. Depending on the app version, permissions are either requested before or after installation.
How are my data collected, processed, and used when accessing the Schnopsn website or using the app without creating a user profile at DonkeyCat?
DonkeyCat GmbH uses the personal data provided by the user or generated during the use of DonkeyCat GmbH services without creating a user profile, without separate consent, exclusively for the execution of the user relationship and as stated in this privacy policy.
When accessing the Schnopsn website or installing the app without creating a user profile, DonkeyCat GmbH collects the following data transmitted by the user's device or browser:
• IP address
• Name of the accessed website, file, date, and time of the request
• Amount of data transferred
• Browser type and version
• Referrer URL ("originating" URL) from which the visitor came to the accessed page
• Requesting provider
Additionally, when merely installing the app without registration or creating a user profile, the following data transmitted by the user's device or browser:
• Push Handle (for sending push notifications)
• Country code
• Language
• Device name
• Name and version of the operating system.
This data is necessary to optimally use the website or app installation and is also used for evaluation for statistical purposes to optimize the service. We process and use these data to prevent and combat fake profiles, illegal activities, and spam, as well as to ensure the integrity and stability of the platform. Furthermore, Donkeycat uses cookies and analysis services.
How are my data collected, processed, and used after creating a user profile and using the app's services?
For display in the app and to inform other players
Donkeycat GmbH uses the personal data communicated by the user or generated after creating a user profile when using Schnopsn, without separate consent, exclusively for the execution of the user relationship and as stated in this privacy policy. For the full online gaming experience, it is necessary for the user to create a user profile. This may involve providing certain personal data that Donkeycat GmbH uses to provide the respective service.
Mandatory information for creating the user profile
When registering and creating a user profile, the following information must be provided:
• Username (pseudonym)
Additionally, the following information can be provided voluntarily:
• Email address
• Password
• Country and state
• Date of birth
• Gender
• Profile photo
These details are collected, processed, and used for the purpose of using the app and are, except for the email address and password, visible to all other users as well as publicly on the website.
Among other things, these data serve for addressing, authentication, age verification, profile personalization, sending game-relevant information (e.g., tournament results), bonus credits, and as a login name.
Game Activities
Game activities are stored by Donkeycat for as long as the account exists to provide the user with game statistics and a consistent history of their Elos and credits. These activities are deleted upon profile deletion or anonymized as necessary for data consistency.
IP Addresses
Chat History During Games
The app offers the possibility to chat with the opponent during a game. The history of this chat is recorded by us for security and verification purposes and stored for 30 days to address misconduct.
Messages in the Message Center
Messages sent from the user's account or sent to the user by other accounts can be deleted by the user at any time.
Account Deletion
The user can have their profile deleted by us at any time and without giving reasons or can delete it themselves in the app. Upon account deletion, existing data are partially anonymized for integrity reasons. After 3 years of inactivity, all user
data are automatically deleted.
Payment Data
In-app purchases, buying credits (the game currency), or purchasing our paid, ad-free app are processed via external payment providers. DonkeyCat GmbH does not collect and process any payment data during a purchase. The input and processing of payment data occur directly with the payment providers. The only data exchanged between DonkeyCat GmbH and the payment providers are technical data (including the transaction ID) for validating purchases.
Minimum Age
The minimum age for using our services is 14 years (completion of the 14th year of life). If you become aware that a person under the age of 14 has unlawfully provided us with personal data, please contact us so that we can delete this information immediately.
Your Rights
You have the right to access, rectification, erasure, restriction, data portability, withdrawal, and objection. If you believe that the processing of your data violates data protection law or your data protection claims have otherwise been violated in any way, you can lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority. In Austria, this is the Data Protection Authority.
Contact Us
If you contact us via the form on the website or by email, the data you provide will be stored by us for six months for the purpose of processing the request and in case of follow-up questions. We do not share these data without your consent.
You can reach us at the following contact details:
DonkeyCat GmbH
